text: The 2014–15 season of the Regionalliga was the 56th season of the third-tier football league in Austria, since its establishment in 1959. ==Regionalliga Ost== ==Regionalliga Mitte== ==Regionalliga West== ==Promotion play-offs== Due to SC Ritzing failure to get a Bundesliga license, SC-ESV Parndorf 1919, who finished second in the Ost division, and SK Austria Klagenfurt, who finished first in the Mitte division, will participate in a two-legged tie. The winner on aggregate score after both matches will be promoted to the Austrian Football First League. ===First leg=== ===Second leg=== ==References== ==External links== * Regionalliga Ost * Regionalliga Mitte * Regionalliga West Category:Austrian Regionalliga seasons Austrian Regional League 3
